Property.preferredDefinition: (ray-dee-AY-shun) A procedure in which radioactive material sealed in needles, seeds, wires, or catheters is placed directly into or near a tumor. Also called brachytherapy, internal radiation, or interstitial radiation.:The process of classifying patients into strata as part of the randomization process or for purposes of data analysis.

Concepts.definition: A type of radiation therapy in which radioactive material is placed inside the body, into a tumor or body cavity.
The process of classifying patients into a sequence of grades or ranks as part of the randomization process or for purposes of data analysis.
